description: Try our easy to follow Squid & Vegetable Stir-fry recipe. Absolutely delicious with the best ingredients from Woolworths.
name: Squid & Vegetable Stir-fry Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 2 leeks, trimmed, cleaned and very thinly sliced
1 red capsicum, deseeded and very thinly sliced
400g squid, cleaned, cut into thick rings

recipeInstructions.text: Heat the oils in a large nonstick wok or frying pan over a high heat. Add the leeks, celery, carrot and red capsicum and stir-fry for about 3-4 minutes until softened.
Add the pak choi, squid and five-spice powder to the pan and stir-fry for about 2-3 minutes until the squid is just cooked through, being careful not to overcook otherwise it will turn rubbery.
Stir in the soy sauce, rice wine and sweet chilli sauce, season with salt and pepper and heat through, stirring. Serve with cooked rice or noodles.
